🚀 Overview
      The Multi-Tool Agent is designed to understand user intent and autonomously select the right tool for the job.
      Instead of just chatting, it can "act" by fetching real-time data or modifying external schedules.

🧠 Core Intelligence
      -AI Agent: Uses LangChain with a defined system prompt to manage logic and tool selection.
      -Model: Powered by Google Gemini (PaLM) for advanced natural language understanding and generation.

📦 Features
      -Intelligent Intent Recognition: Automatically decides whether to answer directly or use a specific tool based on the query.
      -Personalized Interaction: Greets users by their Telegram first and last names.
      -Multi-Platform Connectivity: Seamlessly bridges Telegram messaging with Google Workspace and search engines.
      -HTML Response Support: Sends formatted messages back to Telegram for better readability.

⚙️ Setup & Requirements
  1.Prerequisites
      -An n8n instance (self-hosted or cloud).
      -Telegram Bot: A bot token from @BotFather.
      -Google Gemini API Key: Access via Google AI Studio.
      -SerpAPI Key: For web search capabilities.
      -Google Calendar OAuth2: Credentials to access and modify your calendar.

   2.nstallation
      -Copy the JSON content of the workflow.
      -In your n8n canvas, press Ctrl + V (or Cmd + V) to paste and import the nodes.
      -Configure the credentials for each node (Telegram, Gemini, SerpAPI, and Google Calendar).
      -Set the Telegram Trigger and Telegram Send Message nodes to your specific bot.
      -Activate the workflow.


📝 Example Interactions
     Search: "Who won the game last night?" (Agent uses SerpAPI)
     Math: "What is the difference in days between today and Christmas?" (Agent uses Calculator)
     Schedule: "Add 'Dentist Appointment' to my calendar for next Monday at 10 AM." (Agent uses Google Calendar Tool)


